Context:
George Brown College has an Office of Research and Innovation that functions as a single point of contact for industry partnerships. The college specializes in job-training and market-readiness of students, with facilities to prototype new products and designs for real-world testing. The research mission focuses on industry- and community-problem solving through applied research, commercialization, and scholarship. They prioritize speed to market and enabling partners to access talent and funding. Contact details: research@georgebrown.ca (email), 416-415-2000 (phone), TTY: 1-877-515-5559 (TTY phone), ask.george@georgebrown.ca (general inquiry email).

The college is currently working on a new Research & Innovation website and some pages may be missing during the process. For assistance, contact the Research & Innovation team directly at research@georgebrown.ca. The information provided should not be considered as a representation or warranty. Contact students for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
